The paper discusses the development of parallel and distributed algorithms for association rule mining, which involves data-intensive and computation-intensive tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of grid and cloud platforms for distributed data processing, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to the Distributed Computing sub-category. The use of association rule mining also suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC and cs.DB, followed by cs.Distributed, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
